Bob Evans Farms, Inc. (NASDAQ:BOBE) Experiences Light Trading Volume 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsBob Evans Farms, Inc. (NASDAQ:BOBE) Experiences Light Trading Volume
July 25, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



Trading volume for Bob Evans Farms, Inc. was 5,466 in the last trading session.  Shares saw a steep decrease in trading volume of 98.73% under the normal average daily volume. 
 Traders are a little more bullish on the company considering the downtick in short interest.  The firm realized a fall in short interest between June 15, 2017 and May 31, 2017 of -8.18%.  Short shares fell 63,306 over that period.  With short interest at 710,162 and short average daily volume at 319,192, days to cover is 2.2 and the percentage of shorted shares was 0.04% on May 31. 
 Here are a few other firms who have also updated their positions.   Morgan Stanley downsized its holdings by selling 500 shares a decrease of 100.0% as of 03/31/2017. Morgan Stanley controls 0 shares worth $0. The total value of its holdings decreased 100.0%. As of quarter end Tower Research Capital LLC (trc) had acquired 227 shares growing its position 3,242.9%. The value of the investment in (BOBE) increased from $0 to $15,000 a change of $15,000 for the reporting period.
 As of the end of the quarter Goldman Sachs Group Inc had sold  a total of 85,888 shares trimming its stake by 85.4%. The value in dollars went from $5,352,000 to $954,000 decreasing 82.2% quarter over quarter. Sandell Asset Management cut its investment by shedding 294,461 shares a decrease of 23.3%. Sandell Asset Management now holds 969,200 shares with a value of $62,872,000. The value of the position overall is down by 6.5%.
  On July 19 analysts at Berenberg starting coverage on BOBE by announcing an initial rating of “Buy”. On May 17, 2016 Maxim Group started covering BOBE giving it an initial rating of “Buy”.        Advertisement






 On December 3 the company was upgraded to “Equal-weight” from “Underweight” and a price target of $40.00 was set in a report from Stephens & Co.. On December 3, 2015 Stephens & Co. left the price objective at $40.00 but upgraded the company  to Equal-weight from Underweight.
 On December 2 Oppenheimer maintained a company rating of “Outperform” but lowered the price target  to $45.00 from $50.00. On June 12 the stock rating was upgraded from “Hold” to “Buy” with a current price target of $57.00 in a statement from Miller Tabak.
 The company is down by -0.19% since yesterday’s close of $67.12.  The company announced a dividend that was paid on Monday June 26th, 2017.  The dividend was $0.340 per share for the quarter or $1.36 annualized.  This dividend amount represented a yeild of $2.03.  The ex-dividend date was Thursday the 8th of June 2017. 
 Company chares are trading at $66.99 a bit lower than $69.90, the stock’s 50 day moving average and which is marginally over the 200 day moving average of $63.41.  The 50 day moving average moved down $-2.91 whereas the 200 day average was up by +5.65%. 
 The company currently has a P/E ratio of 10.66 and market capitalization is 1.33B.  In the latest earnings report the EPS was $6.29 and is expected to be $2.23 for the current year with 19,924,000 shares presently outstanding.  Analysts expect next quarter’s EPS will be $0.49 and the next full year EPS is anticipated to be $2.54. 
 Bob Evans Farms, Inc. (Bob Evans), launched on November 4, 1985, is a producer and distributor of refrigerated potato, pasta and vegetable-based side dishes, pork sausage, and a variety of refrigerated and frozen food items under the Bob Evans and Owens or Country Creek brand names. These food products are distributed to customers throughout the United States. Additionally, the Company manufactures and sells similar products to foodservice customers, restaurants and food sellers. The Company operates through BEF Foods segment..
