Bob Evans Farms, Inc. Key Developments

Bob Evans Farms, Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Fourth Quarter and Full Year Ended April 28, 2017; Provides Consolidated Earnings Guidance for the Fiscal Year 2018
Jun 15 17
Bob Evans Farms, Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the fourth quarter and full year ended April 28, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported, on a GAAP basis, net income of $108.9 million, or $5.39 per diluted share, compared with net income of $0.6 million, or $0.03 per diluted share, in the corresponding period last year. Non-GAAP consolidated net income was $12.2 million, or $0.61 per diluted share, compared with non-GAAP net income of $9.5 million, or $0.48 per diluted share, in the corresponding period last year.  Adjusted net sales were $99,923,000 against $95,274,000 a year ago. Net sales from continuing operations were $99.9 million, a decrease of $2.5 million, or 2.4%, compared to $102.4 million in the corresponding period last year. GAAP operating income from continuing operations was $9.5 million, compared to $10.3 million in the corresponding period last year. Non-GAAP operating income from continuing operations was $13.8 million, compared to $11.3 million in the corresponding period last year, an improvement of $2.5 million. The improvement was due primarily to the aforementioned increase in pounds sold and the favorable sales mix of higher-margin side-dish items; partially offset by higher production costs, and increased freight expense resulting from increased pounds sold. 

For the year, the company reported net sales from continuing operations were $394.8 million, an increase of $7.2 million, or 1.9%, compared to $387.6 million in the prior year. GAAP operating income from continuing operations was $30.1 million, compared to $33.1 million in the prior year. Non-GAAP operating income from continuing operations was $53.0 million, compared to $37.7 million in the prior year, an improvement of $15.3 million.  Non-gaap net income from continuing operations was $33,083,000 or $1.64 per diluted share against $19,343,000 or $0.90 per diluted share a year ago. Adjusted net sales were $394,842,000 against $380,496,000 a year ago. The improvement was due primarily to the aforementioned increase in pounds sold and the favorable sales mix of higher-margin side-dish items, partially offset by a $4.9 million increase in trade spending net of lower sow costs, lower average net selling prices and higher production costs and increased freight expense resulting from increased pounds sold. Purchase of property, plant and equipment was $65,768,000 against $65,694,000 a year ago. Net cash provided by operating activities was $73,558,000 against $123,636,000 a year ago.


For the fiscal 2018, Net sales is expected to be in between $464 to $476 million, EBITDA is expected to be in between $102 to $108 million, GAAP diluted earnings per share is expected to be in between $2.06 to $2.24, Capital expenditures is expected to be in between $25 to $30 million, Net interest expense is expected to be in between $3.8 to $4.3 million and GAAP tax rate is expected to be in between 34.5% to 35.5%.


